quasilinearization and the estimationof differential operators from eigenvalues.wgiven a linear ordinary differential operatorcontaining several unknown constants and a number of its eigenvalues, the values of the unknown constantsare estimated.  a precise formulation is provided, and an effective numerical procedure for solution is indicated.  the results of some computational experiments are given.cacm april, bellman, r. e.kagiwada, h. h.kalaba, r. e.vasudenvan, r..kquasilinearization, eigenvalues, differential operators,nonlinear boundary-value problems, inverse problems,differential equations, system identification.c. . .ca jb february ,   : am